[src:dataclasses-json/serialization] Many institutions, such as archives and libraries, attempt to future proof their backup archives—in particular, database dumps—by storing them in some relatively human-readable serialized format.
[src:dataclasses-json/serialization] The Xerox Network Systems Courier technology in the early 1980s influenced the first widely adopted standard.
