[src:dataclasses-json/serialization] In Haskell, serialization is supported for types that are members of the Read and Show type classes.
[src:dataclasses-json/serialization] Every type that is a member of the `Read` type class defines a function that will extract the data from the string representation of the dumped data.
[src:dataclasses-json/serialization] The `Show` type class, in turn, contains the `show` function from which a string representation of the object can be generated.
[src:dataclasses-json/serialization] The programmer need not define the functions explicitly—merely declaring a type to be deriving Read or deriving Show, or both, can make the compiler generate the appropriate functions for many cases (but not all: function types, for example, cannot automatically derive Show or Read).
